3293  for( face_player = FirstPlayerInfo( sh ); face_player; face_player = NextPlayerInfo( sh ))
3294  {
3295  bool has_face_data;
3296 
3297  if( face_player == player )
3298  {
3299  continue;
3300  }
3301  // Don't send face data to modem players for bandwidth reasons
3302  if( player->m_Conn->GetBandwidthType() == Net::Conn::vNARROWBAND )
3303  {
3304  continue;
3305  }
3306 
3307  has_face_data = false;
3308  if( face_player->GetFaceData())
3309  {
3310  has_face_data = true;
3311  }
3312  else
3313  {
3314  if( face_player->IsLocalPlayer())
3315  {
3316  has_face_data = SendFaceDataToServer();
3317  }
3318  }
3319 
3320  if( has_face_data == false )
3321  {
3322  continue;
3323  }
3324 
3325 
3326  m_server->StreamMessageToConn( player->m_Conn, MSG_ID_FACE_DATA, vMAX_FACE_DATA_SIZE + 1, face_player->GetFaceData(), "Face Data",
3327  vSEQ_GROUP_FACE_MSGS, false, true );
3328  }
3329 }

5013  max_skaters = 2;
5014  offset = 0; // reset the offset, so they always get used the same way
5015  }
5016 
5017 
5018  }
5019 
5020  for( i = 0; i < max_skaters; i++ )
5021  {
5022  m_skater_starting_points[i] = -1;
5023  }
5024 
5025  // For each skater, choose a random starting point
5026  for( i = 0; i < max_skaters; i++ )
5027  {
5028  bool unique;
5029 
5030  // Choose a random starting point until it's unique
5031  do
5032  {
5033  m_skater_starting_points[i] = Mth::Rnd( max_skaters );
5034  unique = true;
5035  for( j = 0; j < max_skaters; j++ )
5036  {
5037  // skip myself
5038  if( i == j )
5039  {
5040  continue;
5041  }
5042 
5043  if( m_skater_starting_points[i] == m_skater_starting_points[j] )
5044  {
5045  unique = false;
5046  break;
5047  }
5048  }
5049  } while( !unique );
5050  }
5051 
5052  // Offset these random sequential numbers by a random number so that we pick
5053  // four sequential numbers within a possibly larger range of starting points
5054  for( i = 0; i < max_skaters; i++ )
5055  {
5056  m_skater_starting_points[i] += offset;
5057  }
5058 
5059  m_crown_spawn_point = Mth::Rnd( vNUM_CROWN_SPAWN_POINTS );
5060 }

479  // (Note, we must be running off a CD, as the check is only performed on CD burns)
480  // If we actually BOOT the cd on the dev system, it will think it's
481  // on a regular PS2, and the DNAS test will be performed
